r <span class="abbreviation">PID<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Proportional Integral Derivative"></template></span>. When I searched on <span class="abbreviation">CD<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Chief Delphi"></template></span>, I found out that SparkMax filters the encoder signals, so it causes some latency in the feedback loop. I couldn’t find which thread it was, but the solution was to add a FeedForward. Maybe you can try adding FeedForward if you haven’t yet.</p>","post_number":2,"post_type":1,"posts_count":5,"updated_at":"2024-03-15T20:33:54.484Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":2,"reads":100,"readers_count":99,"score":30.0,"yours":false,"topic_id":458791,"topic_slug":"spark-max-pid-controller-and-trapezoid-profile","display_username":"Yanki K.","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":48849,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":""},"post_url":"/t/spark-max-pid-controller-and-trapezoid-profile/458791/2","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null},{"id":3334045,"name":"Val","username":"Otter502","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/otter502/{size}/245799_2.png","created_at":"2024-03-15T20:50:38.728Z","cooked":"<p>one way to help diagnose the issue is by publishing the applied output to network tables and graphing it via ad